The Salesforce Data Model for Financial Services Cloud

We've adapted the Salesforce data model to create a foundation for industries that require a structured, flexible B2C data model. New custom fields on the Account and Contact standard objects let us model clients. New custom objects let us model client financials, relationship groups, and more.

Data Model Overview
A person is modeled in one of two ways: person accounts or the individual model. Person accounts provide better support for B2C activities and are enabled in FSC trial orgs and new installations.
A group gives insight into a customerâ€™s financial circles, such as a household with its family members and professional connections.
In addition to recording complex, multi-party relationships using groups, Financial Services Cloud also models one-to-one relationships between people and businesses.

Custom objects represent employment and education information. Other assets, liabilities, goals, and revenue are modeled using custom objects. You can either use standard objects or managed package objects to represent financial accounts and the parties involved with their financial accounts.
Standard objects record details about new customer leads and the opportunities to provide customers with new products.

Review the objects that come with Financial Services Cloud using Schema Builder, the data model viewing tool, along with the Object Manager and the Enterprise WSDL file generator.
title: Understanding Salesforce Data Model for Financial Services
